1
00:00:00,265 --> 00:00:02,828
I told you that I understand why you have to work hard.

2
00:00:02,840 --> 00:00:03,988
But please.

3
00:00:04,007 --> 00:00:05,653
You have to take care yourself too.

4
00:00:05,687 --> 00:00:07,268
I just want to do it for you.

5
00:00:07,355 --> 00:00:09,917
You have to promise that you will not overwork yourself.

6
00:00:09,992 --> 00:00:13,108
Also have a proper meal.
Then I won't stop mad at you.

7
00:00:13,265 --> 00:00:14,595
I promise.

8
00:01:46,810 --> 00:01:47,990
Nice. Nice.

9
00:01:48,050 --> 00:01:50,320
Go in. Almost done.

10
00:01:50,440 --> 00:01:51,990
This is the last fort.

11
00:01:52,030 --> 00:01:54,900
Yeah. Like that.

12
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:56,790
Like that.

13
00:01:56,820 --> 00:01:58,740
Done!

14
00:01:59,730 --> 00:02:01,540
1 day before North's birthday.

15
00:02:03,990 --> 00:02:05,740
What is he doing now?

16
00:02:30,700 --> 00:02:32,380
Happy birthday, North.

17
00:03:27,580 --> 00:03:29,110
Hello, P'Jo?

18
00:03:29,720 --> 00:03:31,680
You just got off work?

19
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:35,030
Um...are you asleep?

20
00:03:35,190 --> 00:03:37,020
Not yet.

21
00:03:37,130 --> 00:03:39,030
Don't tell me you're waiting for me.

22
00:03:39,190 --> 00:03:42,740
- Err--
- I told you to go straight to sleep.

23
00:03:43,210 --> 00:03:46,920
Hey. I just want to talk to you.

24
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:48,210
Stubborn.

25
00:03:50,810 --> 00:03:53,220
And...are you arrived at your room?

26
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:56,020
Not yet. I just left the office.

27
00:03:56,070 --> 00:03:57,940
Woah. Just finished?

28
00:03:58,300 --> 00:03:59,600
Um.

29
00:04:00,250 --> 00:04:01,420
North.

30
00:04:04,590 --> 00:04:06,170
Happy birthday.

31
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,150
Yes.

32
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:09,560
Thank you.

33
00:04:11,470 --> 00:04:13,240
Am I the first one?

34
00:04:13,950 --> 00:04:15,650
Actually....

35
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:18,740
there's Ter who called me earlier.

36
00:04:19,250 --> 00:04:21,620
But he called before midnight.

37
00:04:21,660 --> 00:04:23,050
So...that doesn't count.

38
00:04:23,730 --> 00:04:25,450
But after midnight,

39
00:04:26,770 --> 00:04:28,280
you're the first one, P'Jo.

40
00:04:28,590 --> 00:04:29,980
Should I wish you something?

41
00:04:29,980 --> 00:04:31,470
It's fine.

42
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:35,320
I bet you're not very good at wishing for people.

43
00:04:37,670 --> 00:04:40,110
I'm sorry I couldn't be there with you today.

44
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,680
You're here now.

45
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,950
In a call like this?

46
00:04:45,470 --> 00:04:47,140
Just hearing your voice...

47
00:04:47,290 --> 00:04:48,750
I'm already happy with that.

48
00:04:50,660 --> 00:04:51,910
P'Jo.

49
00:04:52,570 --> 00:04:53,480
Hmm?

50
00:04:56,060 --> 00:04:57,300
I miss you.

51
00:04:59,410 --> 00:05:01,220
And don't drive so fast.

52
00:05:01,290 --> 00:05:04,600
Even if it's already late at night and there're less cars,

53
00:05:04,990 --> 00:05:07,110
but you still need to drive carefully.

54
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:08,850
Understood.

55
00:05:09,030 --> 00:05:11,230
And can you talk on the phone while driving?

56
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:15,680
If I can't do it why would I call you?

57
00:05:16,650 --> 00:05:20,000
And...how's your work today?

58
00:05:22,070 --> 00:05:23,030
Well...

59
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,830
It was not good.

60
00:05:27,770 --> 00:05:29,350
Are you okay?

61
00:05:30,940 --> 00:05:32,170
Not really.

62
00:05:35,030 --> 00:05:36,970
Do you mind telling me?

63
00:05:37,940 --> 00:05:39,350
About what?

64
00:05:39,730 --> 00:05:42,400
About your work today.

65
00:05:42,490 --> 00:05:44,070
Oh it's nothing.

66
00:05:47,150 --> 00:05:50,200
But I would love to hear it.

67
00:05:50,380 --> 00:05:51,650
Please, P'Jo.

68
00:05:51,770 --> 00:05:54,980
Please. Tell me.

69
00:05:55,130 --> 00:05:56,170
Well...

70
00:05:56,900 --> 00:05:59,110
there were some changes within the team.

71
00:05:59,110 --> 00:06:00,710
And they didn't update each other.

72
00:06:00,710 --> 00:06:02,670
So when there's a mistake,

73
00:06:03,110 --> 00:06:04,380
they also didn't tell me.

74
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:07,590
But at the end,
sI'm the one who solves all the problems.

75
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:11,730
It's your birthday.

76
00:06:12,220 --> 00:06:14,050
Why do you wanna hear about my work?

77
00:06:15,820 --> 00:06:17,190
It's fine.

78
00:06:17,260 --> 00:06:19,770
I would love to hear anything about you.

79
00:06:20,980 --> 00:06:24,530
But everything is settled now, right?

80
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:27,140
Not yet.

81
00:06:27,870 --> 00:06:30,320
Even I don't really know much about your work,

82
00:06:31,130 --> 00:06:33,150
but I will always be by your side, P'Jo.

83
00:06:33,470 --> 00:06:35,450
Let's hug to charge our battery.

84
00:06:36,550 --> 00:06:37,660
Come on.

85
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:43,070
I'm sorry I couldn't be there for you either.

86
00:06:43,390 --> 00:06:44,880
That's fine.

87
00:06:45,180 --> 00:06:47,630
Hearing your voice already makes me feel better.

88
00:06:47,630 --> 00:06:50,700
Wow. You make me wanna squeeze through the phone and be with you there.

89
00:06:50,700 --> 00:06:51,230
Clingy?

90
00:06:51,230 --> 00:06:51,240
Yes, I wanna be clingy.
Clingy?

91
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:53,940
Yes, I wanna be clingy.

92
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:56,630
Can I see your clingy face?

93
00:07:05,150 --> 00:07:08,110
Ugh. P'Jo.
You're such a cheator.

94
00:07:08,190 --> 00:07:09,470
You're not gonna turn on your camera?

95
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:10,630
No.

96
00:07:10,970 --> 00:07:14,630
Why not? Turn it on.
I wanna see your face.

97
00:07:14,900 --> 00:07:15,970
Please.

98
00:07:16,140 --> 00:07:18,230
Please turn it on.

99
00:07:18,300 --> 00:07:20,910
Woah. You're wearing a suit?

100
00:07:21,020 --> 00:07:23,160
Um. I had a meeting earlier this morning.

101
00:07:24,060 --> 00:07:27,390
I actually have never seen you in a suit before.

102
00:07:27,910 --> 00:07:29,120
It's to hot to wear it.

103
00:07:29,360 --> 00:07:32,970
And you're still continue working?

104
00:07:33,230 --> 00:07:35,110
Um...a little.

105
00:07:36,230 --> 00:07:37,540
This reminds me of that time.

106
00:07:37,660 --> 00:07:39,190
What are you talking about?

107
00:07:39,570 --> 00:07:41,500
When we first talked.

108
00:07:42,020 --> 00:07:43,550
When we called...

109
00:07:43,550 --> 00:07:46,630
...and I just fell asleep
while I waited for you to work.

110
00:07:47,030 --> 00:07:48,140
Oh.

111
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:49,910
And...

112
00:07:50,350 --> 00:07:54,370
do I have to be quiet? Not to disturb you this time?

113
00:07:54,530 --> 00:07:55,380
No need.

114
00:07:55,430 --> 00:07:57,710
Hey then why did I have to do it back then?

115
00:07:57,900 --> 00:07:59,490
Cause I was not used to your voice.

116
00:08:00,040 --> 00:08:02,530
I can talk now then?

117
00:08:02,700 --> 00:08:03,900
I'm not stopping you.

118
00:08:06,470 --> 00:08:08,060
I have...

119
00:08:08,630 --> 00:08:10,670
a question for you, P'Jo.

120
00:08:11,030 --> 00:08:12,580
What is it?

121
00:08:13,050 --> 00:08:15,080
When you met me for the first time...

122
00:08:15,660 --> 00:08:18,430
can you tell me what it felt like for you?

123
00:08:20,380 --> 00:08:22,370
The firs time we met?

124
00:08:23,150 --> 00:08:24,830
At the bar?

125
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:26,430
Yes.

126
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:28,870
I'm so mad, of course.

127
00:08:30,820 --> 00:08:32,700
I understand why.

128
00:08:33,150 --> 00:08:36,990
- You didn't have to be so cruel to me though.
- But you deserved it, didn't you?

129
00:08:40,500 --> 00:08:42,900
- I did.
- Um.

130
00:08:43,290 --> 00:08:45,560
I could scold you with literally everything you did.

131
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:47,200
Got in a fight in a bar?

132
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:49,620
Working behind my back
and put yourself in danger?

133
00:08:51,590 --> 00:08:53,670
You worried me everyday.

134
00:08:55,170 --> 00:08:57,510
I shouldn't have asked
to get myself scolded at.

135
00:09:01,220 --> 00:09:02,910
P'Jo.

136
00:09:04,020 --> 00:09:05,760
My mom asked...

137
00:09:06,030 --> 00:09:09,250
that you're not going to visit her during the break?

138
00:09:09,830 --> 00:09:11,950
Oh sure...but...

139
00:09:12,290 --> 00:09:14,090
when my work is done.

140
00:09:14,430 --> 00:09:17,030
Okay. Just let me know when.

141
00:09:17,540 --> 00:09:19,630
I will have everything prepared nicely.

142
00:09:22,010 --> 00:09:24,840
Oh and how's your birthday?

143
00:09:25,780 --> 00:09:28,560
Just like any other year. Nothing special.

144
00:09:28,710 --> 00:09:31,060
I didn't have a party or anything.

145
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:33,270
But my mom bought me a gift.

146
00:09:33,370 --> 00:09:34,460
What is it?

147
00:09:34,610 --> 00:09:36,380
She got me a pair shoes.

148
00:09:36,670 --> 00:09:39,820
And do you want anything else?
I haven't bought you anything.

149
00:09:39,830 --> 00:09:43,150
Woah. You already gave me so many things.

150
00:09:43,940 --> 00:09:45,620
Then...

151
00:09:47,700 --> 00:09:50,970
can I ask you for something else?

152
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:53,930
What is it?

153
00:09:55,510 --> 00:09:57,250
P'Jo...

154
00:09:58,110 --> 00:10:01,710
can you tell me that you love me?

155
00:10:02,380 --> 00:10:05,220
- That's it?
- Woah...it's not 'That's it'.

156
00:10:05,380 --> 00:10:08,360
Please. Tell me that you love me.

157
00:10:15,010 --> 00:10:17,090
I love you, North.

158
00:10:18,770 --> 00:10:20,770
I love you too, P'Jo.

159
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:28,730
- If I was there, you're not gonna get away from me.
- Huh!? What do you mean?

160
00:10:29,030 --> 00:10:33,190
Nothing. I just wanna tell you that please be less cute.

161
00:10:36,730 --> 00:10:38,090
Go to sleep.

162
00:10:38,180 --> 00:10:42,110
But I wanna talk to you.

163
00:10:42,610 --> 00:10:44,800
Go to sleep. I will be here.

164
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,270
Okay.

165
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:04,180
I wanna be with you.

166
00:11:05,370 --> 00:11:09,890
You're probably so tired recently.

167
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:12,670
You want me to leave work behind
and come see you?

168
00:11:12,740 --> 00:11:14,520
No.

169
00:11:15,090 --> 00:11:17,380
Then don't be so cute like this.

170
00:11:17,490 --> 00:11:19,660
If not, then I might need to leave my work.

171
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:23,280
I'm sleepy now.

172
00:11:23,650 --> 00:11:25,430
Go to sleep then. I will be here.

173
00:11:25,830 --> 00:11:28,650
No. I will be the one who stays up.

174
00:11:28,770 --> 00:11:30,790
You're still working.

175
00:11:30,910 --> 00:11:34,630
- Go to sleep. I will be here with you.
- No, I can't.

176
00:11:34,810 --> 00:11:36,890
I will be the one who stays up for you.

177
00:11:38,010 --> 00:11:39,530
You're stubborn.

178
00:11:40,770 --> 00:11:42,720
I got it from you.

179
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:46,710
You're really good at arguing lately.

180
00:12:28,230 --> 00:12:29,890
Ter.

181
00:12:30,650 --> 00:12:32,940
Enjoy your trip.

182
00:12:34,450 --> 00:12:36,740
P'Hill.

183
00:12:44,870 --> 00:12:46,460
Johan.

184
00:12:49,100 --> 00:12:50,540
Hello?

185
00:12:50,710 --> 00:12:52,570
You're still up?

186
00:12:52,660 --> 00:12:55,670
Yes, why did you answer me so quickly?

187
00:12:55,820 --> 00:12:57,690
You said you're sleepy.

188
00:12:58,580 --> 00:13:00,610
I just wokee up.

189
00:13:00,740 --> 00:13:03,340
Probably cause I miss you too much.

190
00:13:03,910 --> 00:13:05,880
You're done working now?

191
00:13:06,010 --> 00:13:08,150
- Yes.
- Really?

192
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:09,530
Why finished early?

193
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:11,550
You said you have so many things to do.

194
00:13:11,650 --> 00:13:13,010
But it's done now.

195
00:13:13,910 --> 00:13:15,570
You're so good.

196
00:13:15,830 --> 00:13:18,170
You're the most talented person in the entire world.

197
00:13:18,210 --> 00:13:20,890
Are you gonna go back to sleep?

198
00:13:21,070 --> 00:13:23,580
Yeah I think I will.

199
00:13:23,900 --> 00:13:25,110
Really?

200
00:13:25,250 --> 00:13:29,450
Yes, I'm still on the bed. Didn't get up or anything.

201
00:13:29,580 --> 00:13:32,710
If you're gonna go back to sleep,
and why the lights are still on?

202
00:13:33,250 --> 00:13:35,210
How do you know?

203
00:13:35,690 --> 00:13:37,540
Open your window.

204
00:13:45,640 --> 00:13:47,570
A delivery for you sir.

205
00:13:48,330 --> 00:13:50,710
Special delivery just for my boyfriend.

206
00:13:52,430 --> 00:13:54,910
Sure. I'm coming down.

207
00:13:56,810 --> 00:13:58,690
Be careful.

208
00:14:12,180 --> 00:14:14,180
Happy birthday.

209
00:14:27,110 --> 00:14:28,890
Thank you.

210
00:14:29,340 --> 00:14:31,530
Thank you so much.

211
00:14:44,270 --> 00:14:48,930
I thought you said 'it's fine.'

212
00:14:51,180 --> 00:14:55,030
I really am. It's fine if you cannot be here.

213
00:14:57,090 --> 00:15:00,310
But it's definitely better if you're here.

214
00:15:02,300 --> 00:15:04,230
Better than from the phone?

215
00:15:04,610 --> 00:15:06,820
Yes, so much better.

216
00:16:25,310 --> 00:16:27,130
You're probably exhausted.

217
00:16:27,300 --> 00:16:30,860
You worked so hard, and still come see me.

218
00:16:31,300 --> 00:16:32,910
Exhaustion is all gone.

219
00:16:42,830 --> 00:16:44,550
What's this?

220
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,300
It's--. Err...

221
00:16:48,810 --> 00:16:50,170
It's...

222
00:16:54,270 --> 00:16:58,780
It probably caught my hand when I packed my things.

223
00:17:00,270 --> 00:17:04,580
I didn't mean to bring this with me when I packed.
I swear.

224
00:17:05,830 --> 00:17:07,290
Really.

225
00:17:13,730 --> 00:17:16,090
I remember it was in the closet, wasn't it?

226
00:17:16,430 --> 00:17:19,150
Or I have bad memory?

227
00:17:28,620 --> 00:17:29,930
Yes.

228
00:17:31,770 --> 00:17:34,180
I took it with me.

229
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:37,270
Why?

230
00:17:38,110 --> 00:17:41,170
Cause I cannot sleep.

231
00:17:49,430 --> 00:17:51,130
Cannot sleep?

232
00:17:56,410 --> 00:17:59,290
Cause I'm not used to this.

233
00:17:59,610 --> 00:18:02,260
I normally go to bed hugging you everyday.

234
00:18:02,630 --> 00:18:05,520
When you're not around, I couldn't sleep.

235
00:18:08,630 --> 00:18:10,320
At least...

236
00:18:11,080 --> 00:18:13,350
I still have your smell.

237
00:18:17,740 --> 00:18:19,360
Please do not...

238
00:18:20,170 --> 00:18:23,030
Do not tease me. I'm begging you.

239
00:18:26,630 --> 00:18:28,250
Ok I won't.

240
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:32,380
Then...

241
00:18:32,630 --> 00:18:34,450
you don't need this shirt anymore.

242
00:18:50,120 --> 00:18:52,380
Stop it.

243
00:18:52,590 --> 00:18:54,370
You need to rest.

244
00:18:58,060 --> 00:18:59,610
Sweet dream.

245
00:19:01,180 --> 00:19:02,470
Sweet dream, baby.

246
00:20:07,880 --> 00:20:09,470
I love you so much.

247
00:20:09,600 --> 00:20:11,290
Did you know that?

248
00:20:54,290 --> 00:20:56,050
Where are you going?

249
00:20:56,290 --> 00:20:59,950
I will go cook.

250
00:21:00,230 --> 00:21:02,670
And prepare stuff for my birthday merit making.

251
00:21:03,130 --> 00:21:04,920
Are you coming with me?

252
00:21:06,070 --> 00:21:07,750
Sure.

253
00:21:08,520 --> 00:21:09,870
Then...

254
00:21:10,330 --> 00:21:14,050
you can continue your sleep.
I will go prep things.

255
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:15,200
Um.

256
00:21:42,900 --> 00:21:46,230
North. I already prepared food for you and P'Jo.

257
00:21:46,270 --> 00:21:50,630
Don't forget to go make some merits.
I have some errands to do today. Will be back later tonight.

258
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:52,610
Woah.

259
00:21:53,120 --> 00:21:54,540
My mom...

260
00:21:55,810 --> 00:21:57,770
sneaked out again?

261
00:22:01,310 --> 00:22:02,920
P'Jo.

262
00:22:03,830 --> 00:22:05,110
P'Johan.

263
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:08,040
Thank you.

264
00:22:08,590 --> 00:22:09,780
P'Jo.

265
00:22:09,900 --> 00:22:13,300
We'll go make birthday merits
and can I stop by to visit my dad a bit?

266
00:22:13,980 --> 00:22:14,910
Of course.

267
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:19,280
I never asked you this...

268
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:22,080
...but are you a buddhist?

269
00:22:25,260 --> 00:22:26,890
Can you go to the temple then?

270
00:22:27,130 --> 00:22:28,750
I can. It's okay.

271
00:23:02,150 --> 00:23:03,160
P'Jo.

272
00:23:03,570 --> 00:23:05,390
This is my dad.

273
00:23:05,450 --> 00:23:06,590
His name is Ko.

274
00:23:09,690 --> 00:23:10,750
Dad.

275
00:23:10,870 --> 00:23:13,660
This is P'Jo.

276
00:23:14,340 --> 00:23:16,550
He's my precious boyfriend.

277
00:23:17,940 --> 00:23:20,050
You might not look as hot as him...

278
00:23:20,510 --> 00:23:22,840
but that's okay. You don't have to be jealous.

279
00:23:23,830 --> 00:23:25,550
At least mom...

280
00:23:25,900 --> 00:23:28,780
