00:44:55,400 --> 00:44:56,580
So dang cute.

561
00:44:59,430 --> 00:45:01,390
You really complimented me.

562
00:45:08,490 --> 00:45:09,600
I will put it here.

563
00:45:10,910 --> 00:45:13,510
Where do you think I should put this?

564
00:45:14,530 --> 00:45:18,030
It should be here,
cause we already have something big there.

565
00:45:18,200 --> 00:45:19,300
Here?

566
00:45:19,680 --> 00:45:20,790
No.

567
00:45:22,380 --> 00:45:24,260
- Not so pretty.
- Too low?

568
00:45:24,570 --> 00:45:25,790
- Here then.
- Here.

569
00:45:48,610 --> 00:45:50,690
Where are you taking me?

570
00:45:51,190 --> 00:45:52,770
I have a present for you.

571
00:45:53,080 --> 00:45:54,140
What present?

572
00:45:56,890 --> 00:45:58,870
Is it a new game?

573
00:46:00,220 --> 00:46:03,110
But there's nothing coming out though.

574
00:46:03,230 --> 00:46:05,440
Hey. Or is it gold?

575
00:46:05,700 --> 00:46:08,050
I really love gold, P'Jo.

576
00:46:08,670 --> 00:46:09,700
No, it's not.

577
00:46:09,900 --> 00:46:12,040
- Hey.
- I'm about to open your eyes.

578
00:46:23,720 --> 00:46:25,820
The claw machine?

579
00:46:26,230 --> 00:46:27,290
Um.

580
00:46:28,280 --> 00:46:30,850
Cause someone said 'he wants a gift'
when we were boyfriends.

581
00:46:30,850 --> 00:46:32,520
So I got him a claw machine.

582
00:46:32,970 --> 00:46:34,020
Cute, right?

583
00:46:35,270 --> 00:46:38,500
I totally thought it was gold I'm getting.

584
00:46:42,280 --> 00:46:44,530
P'Jo. I'm kidding.

585
00:46:44,930 --> 00:46:46,500
This is cute.

586
00:46:46,740 --> 00:46:47,730
But why...

587
00:46:47,920 --> 00:46:50,540
there's only one turtle in there?

588
00:46:52,850 --> 00:46:54,950
They probably forgot to take it out.
Let me complain them.

589
00:46:54,950 --> 00:46:56,210
Hey. That's okay.

590
00:46:56,610 --> 00:46:58,900
I think it's cute.

591
00:47:00,510 --> 00:47:02,660
I will try to catch it tonight.

592
00:47:03,880 --> 00:47:04,960
I'm gonna go for it.

593
00:47:08,040 --> 00:47:09,120
Here we go.

594
00:47:17,580 --> 00:47:18,710
Hey.

595
00:47:19,340 --> 00:47:21,330
Hey. P'Jo.

596
00:47:21,500 --> 00:47:22,830
I got it.

597
00:47:22,900 --> 00:47:23,860
With your first attempt?

598
00:47:23,870 --> 00:47:25,070
Hey.

599
00:47:28,100 --> 00:47:29,350
P'Jo. It's so cute.

600
00:47:30,440 --> 00:47:32,160
It even looks uglier than that one.

601
00:47:32,160 --> 00:47:33,150
Hey.

602
00:47:33,190 --> 00:47:34,260
How come?

603
00:47:34,710 --> 00:47:35,820
He's such a cutie.

604
00:47:39,490 --> 00:47:42,800
Come on, P'Jo.
You promised me that you're gonna do it.

605
00:47:42,870 --> 00:47:44,310
Come on.

606
00:47:47,110 --> 00:47:48,350
Let me tie it for you.

607
00:47:59,020 --> 00:48:00,240
That'a not it.

608
00:48:01,580 --> 00:48:02,990
You still need this.

609
00:48:10,510 --> 00:48:11,910
Cute!

610
00:48:18,430 --> 00:48:19,480
Why are you smiling?

611
00:48:19,740 --> 00:48:20,890
Hey cause...

612
00:48:21,150 --> 00:48:23,940
you're wearing an apron and looks so cute.

613
00:48:24,620 --> 00:48:26,180
Let me see.

614
00:48:26,430 --> 00:48:27,870
Let me see what you're filming.

615
00:48:28,860 --> 00:48:30,450
Do not delete it.

616
00:48:35,610 --> 00:48:37,590
You're pretty good at filming too.

617
00:48:38,000 --> 00:48:39,040
Thank you.

618
00:48:39,340 --> 00:48:41,210
Shall we start?

619
00:48:42,370 --> 00:48:43,770
- Here.
- And...

620
00:48:43,890 --> 00:48:45,050
where do I begin?

621
00:48:45,390 --> 00:48:47,300
You mix the eggs first.

622
00:48:47,860 --> 00:48:50,070
Crack the eggs and mix it all up.

623
00:48:51,650 --> 00:48:53,850
Cookies are not that expensive, aren't they?

624
00:48:54,560 --> 00:48:55,510
What did you just say?

625
00:48:55,520 --> 00:48:57,090
Oh nothing.

626
00:48:57,560 --> 00:49:00,100
- Mix the eggs right? Crack it first?
- Yes. Yes.

627
00:49:01,770 --> 00:49:03,270
P'Jo. You should do it here.

628
00:49:04,840 --> 00:49:07,390
The shell is in the bowl now.

629
00:49:11,040 --> 00:49:13,990
P'Jo. You need to mix it like this.

630
00:49:14,090 --> 00:49:17,500
Look how I do it. 1 2 3.
Swirl it like this.

631
00:49:18,610 --> 00:49:21,150
Again.

632
00:49:21,800 --> 00:49:23,300
Do it.

633
00:49:23,560 --> 00:49:24,830
You're teasing me again.

634
00:49:25,560 --> 00:49:28,880
Guys look. This guy is teasing me.

635
00:49:31,150 --> 00:49:33,030
I'm not.

636
00:49:38,890 --> 00:49:41,250
It was really yummy,
the cookies that made by you.

637
00:49:41,260 --> 00:49:42,840
I didn't do anything.

638
00:49:42,890 --> 00:49:44,630
I just mix everything together.

639
00:49:44,710 --> 00:49:47,300
Really? It's really good.

640
00:49:48,320 --> 00:49:49,650
Um.

641
00:49:50,070 --> 00:49:51,400
Just a blink of an eye,

642
00:49:51,550 --> 00:49:53,510
we've been together for a year already.

643
00:49:53,510 --> 00:49:54,920
Let's do a quick recap...

644
00:49:55,000 --> 00:49:55,730
of what...

645
00:49:55,810 --> 00:49:57,060
we went through this year.

646
00:49:57,950 --> 00:49:59,360
What about you?

647
00:49:59,610 --> 00:50:00,700
How was yours?

648
00:50:03,180 --> 00:50:06,150
You came to my life this year,
it's been the best year so far.

649
00:50:06,240 --> 00:50:07,600
What about you?

650
00:50:07,760 --> 00:50:08,920
Me too.

651
00:50:10,270 --> 00:50:12,530
It was one hell of a year.

652
00:50:12,620 --> 00:50:14,170
So many things happened.

653
00:50:14,460 --> 00:50:15,230
Since...

654
00:50:15,240 --> 00:50:16,350
the moment I woke up...

655
00:50:16,600 --> 00:50:17,990
...and had a debt.

656
00:50:18,300 --> 00:50:19,390
But at the end,

657
00:50:19,510 --> 00:50:22,310
...plot twist.
My creditor has become my boyfriend.

658
00:50:22,310 --> 00:50:23,180
Haaaa.

659
00:50:26,680 --> 00:50:29,350
I have a question to ask you today as well.

660
00:50:30,570 --> 00:50:31,520
What?

661
00:50:32,720 --> 00:50:35,670
If you could wish for 3 things,

662
00:50:35,960 --> 00:50:37,080
what would your wishes be?

663
00:50:37,080 --> 00:50:38,090
3 wishes, right?

664
00:50:38,840 --> 00:50:40,180
I'll give all the wishes to you.

665
00:50:40,500 --> 00:50:41,860
Then I'll have 6 wishes?

666
00:50:41,890 --> 00:50:42,780
Um.

667
00:50:44,070 --> 00:50:45,250
What should I wish for?

668
00:50:46,680 --> 00:50:51,250
I will ask my favorite game company

669
00:50:51,500 --> 00:50:53,280
to produce a lot of new games.

670
00:50:53,450 --> 00:50:54,200
And...

671
00:50:54,280 --> 00:50:56,730
I'd wish for myself to have more money to buy their games.

672
00:50:56,730 --> 00:50:59,210
I would wish to have time to play those games.

673
00:50:59,540 --> 00:51:03,920
And I wish for myself, you, mom,

674
00:51:04,800 --> 00:51:07,380
and eveyone around us to be so happy.

675
00:51:08,580 --> 00:51:11,140
And lastly...

676
00:51:11,570 --> 00:51:13,300
I'd wish for myself to win a lottery.

677
00:51:13,470 --> 00:51:14,950
Even at least the last 3 digits.

678
00:51:15,100 --> 00:51:17,170
You really wanna win a lottery that bad?

679
00:51:17,860 --> 00:51:20,810
- Do you want the 2st prize? I will transfer for you.
- Wow.

680
00:51:20,980 --> 00:51:22,470
You don't get me.

681
00:51:22,590 --> 00:51:23,700
What I'm wishing for...

682
00:51:23,720 --> 00:51:25,530
...is to make money for our household.

683
00:51:26,080 --> 00:51:28,660
But if you give it to me,

684
00:51:28,760 --> 00:51:30,740
the money is the same amount.

685
00:51:31,490 --> 00:51:33,070
Yeah. I don't get it.

686
00:51:33,280 --> 00:51:35,480
And anything else you would like to ask me?

687
00:51:38,300 --> 00:51:40,510
I wanna ask you...

688
00:51:40,690 --> 00:51:43,300
whether you have anything
that you wish I could change?

689
00:51:43,450 --> 00:51:46,640
Or anything that you don't like about me?

690
00:51:46,880 --> 00:51:49,050
Nothing. You?

691
00:51:49,480 --> 00:51:50,640
For me?

692
00:51:50,810 --> 00:51:52,660
If I'd have to change...

693
00:51:53,550 --> 00:51:56,100
I would like to be more discrete.

694
00:51:56,180 --> 00:51:58,090
Cause I think I'm too funny and immature.

695
00:52:01,730 --> 00:52:04,240
I meant anything that you would like me to change?

696
00:52:05,540 --> 00:52:07,670
See. I'm being funny again.

697
00:52:09,600 --> 00:52:10,710
For you?

698
00:52:12,060 --> 00:52:13,320
I think...

699
00:52:13,810 --> 00:52:15,200
you don't need to change anything.

700
00:52:15,200 --> 00:52:17,210
Cause you're already perfect.

701
00:52:19,110 --> 00:52:21,080
Last question.

702
00:52:22,230 --> 00:52:25,660
Do you have any questions that you wouldn't dare to ask me?

703
00:52:29,340 --> 00:52:30,790
Every time I look at you,

704
00:52:30,870 --> 00:52:32,430
I always have one question in mind.

705
00:52:33,610 --> 00:52:34,530
What is it?

706
00:52:36,610 --> 00:52:38,590
Who is this kid?

707
00:52:38,790 --> 00:52:40,090
Where is he from?

708
00:52:40,290 --> 00:52:42,060
How can he make me so in love with him?

709
00:52:43,280 --> 00:52:44,760
Me too.

710
00:52:45,230 --> 00:52:47,270
I also have a question.

711
00:52:48,240 --> 00:52:50,390
Like who is this guy?

712
00:52:50,670 --> 00:52:53,130
Who send him to me to make me happy in everyday?

713
00:53:01,130 --> 00:53:03,360
Please be with me like this every year, okay?

714
00:53:03,360 --> 00:53:05,690
Christmas and start a new year together.

715
00:53:06,570 --> 00:53:07,930
Be together forever.

716
00:53:10,180 --> 00:53:11,200
Sure.

717
00:53:12,050 --> 00:53:13,890
I will be with you forever.

718
00:53:37,370 --> 00:53:39,070
Whch one do you like better?

719
00:53:40,840 --> 00:53:42,420
i like them both equally.

720
00:53:42,560 --> 00:53:45,060
And you gave both of them to me.

721
00:53:46,030 --> 00:53:46,720
And...

722
00:53:46,850 --> 00:53:49,690
why don't you like this stupid ducky?

723
00:53:52,000 --> 00:53:55,390
It is even the first gift you gave me.

724
00:53:55,610 --> 00:53:58,230
Even though we didn't know each other
when we first met.

725
00:53:58,740 --> 00:54:00,630
Because it was the first gift,

726
00:54:00,810 --> 00:54:03,110
and I wanted to buy something nicer for you.

727
00:54:03,750 --> 00:54:04,570
And...

728
00:54:04,810 --> 00:54:06,810
what's wrong with this stupid ducky?

729
00:54:06,960 --> 00:54:08,420
Look at his face.

730
00:54:09,040 --> 00:54:10,700
Even you call him stupid ducky.

731
00:54:10,790 --> 00:54:12,990
He looks stupid but he's still cute though.

732
00:54:14,030 --> 00:54:16,980
Only his own mother would say he's cute.

733
00:54:17,210 --> 00:54:20,300
Poor thing. Let me see.

734
00:54:20,470 --> 00:54:22,340
What?
Your daddy doesn't love you?

735
00:54:22,500 --> 00:54:23,860
What!?

736
00:54:24,700 --> 00:54:26,880
Cause daddy can only love mommy.

737
00:54:27,840 --> 00:54:28,960
P'Jo.

738
00:54:29,020 --> 00:54:31,240
What are you doing? Playing house?

739
00:54:32,670 --> 00:54:34,100
I better sleep.

740
00:54:40,620 --> 00:54:42,070
Kiss me agiain?

741
00:54:42,350 --> 00:54:44,110
All day long.
